olive oil
1 bag baby broccoli
1 packet pork mince
1 packet udon noodles
1 packet garlic paste
1 box coconut milk
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet ponzu sauce
1 bag coriander
1 packet Roasted Peanuts & Cashew Mix
1 packet Roasted Pumpkin

• Boil the kettle. Trim and halve baby
broccoli
• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over
high heat
• Cook pork, breaking up with a spoon,
until just browned, 4-5 mins

• Meanwhile, heat a saucepan over
medium-high heat. Half-fill with
boiling water
• Cook udon noodles until tender,
3-4 mins
• In last min of cook time, gently stir
noodles with a fork to separate
• Drain, rinse and set aside

• To pan with pork, add baby broccoli
and cook until tender, 5-6 mins
• Add roasted pumpkin, garlic paste
and cook until fragrant, 1 min
• Add coconut milk, seasoning, ponzu
and cook until slightly reduced,
1-2 mins
• Add drained noodles. Toss to
combine
• Plate up pork and veggie noodles
• Tear over coriander and garnish with
cashew mix to serve